<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-454-764  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 454 764.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  July 25 1989 n1227* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Kao to do 3.5&quot; disks in US, Spain. (Kao Corp)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Kao Corp. (products).andO;Topic:     Floppy DiskManufacturingSpain3.5&quot; Disk.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>KAO TO DO 3.5&quot; DISKS IN US, SPAINandM;Kao Corp of Japan, whose core business is primary products for the cosmeticsand det-ergent industries, has joined the rush of Japanese corporations inmature industries to diversify into computer-related technologies, and it hasformed Kao Corp Espana SA to make 3.5&quot; floppy disks for the European market,and plans a similar plant in Plymouth, Massachusetts.andP;  Kao plans to invest$34m in the Spanish venture this year and it looks to have the plant up andrunning by mid-1990, producing 3m floppy disks a month, with about 90% goingfor export because there is as yet insufficient Spanish demand to mop up morethan a small fraction of planned output.andP;  Kao is also planning to invest $68min Spain over the next five years in its core chemicals businesses.andP;  The USplant is rather bigger, with capacity of 6m disks a month and will cost $60m,employing 160 at capacity, planned for the year-end.andO;</TEXT></DOC>